        {"@type":"Question","name":"How do I check company name availability in the UK?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Use our free company names search tool. Enter your desired name and it instantly queries the live Companies House register - over 5 million companies. Results show existing active and dissolved companies so you can assess whether your chosen name clears the too-like rule. Once clear, proceed to ltd company UK registration via our same-day formation service."}},
        {"@type":"Question","name":"What does check for company name availability actually involve?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Checking for company name availability means running your proposed name through three tests: (1) the Companies House same-as comparison against 5 million+ registered names, (2) the sensitive words list under the Company Names Regulations 2015, and (3) optionally the UK IPO trademark database to rule out brand conflicts."}},
        {"@type":"Question","name":"What are ltd company names and what are the rules?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Ltd company names are official trading names for private limited companies registered at Companies House. Every valid UK ltd company name must end in Limited or Ltd, must not be too like an existing name, must not include restricted words without approval, must not imply a government connection, and must not be offensive."}},
        {"@type":"Question","name":"What does Too Like mean under UK company name rules?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A name is considered too like an existing name if it differs only by common words, punctuation, spacing, or generic suffixes. For example Plumbing London Ltd is legally identical to Plumbing London Group Ltd. Companies House will automatically reject the duplicate. Our search highlights potential too-like matches before your new ltd company registration."}},
        {"@type":"Question","name":"Can I reserve a company name without incorporating?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. Companies House does not permit name reservations. The only way to secure and protect a ltd company name is to actively incorporate it - either as a trading company or as a dormant shell for future use. Our same-day ltd company UK registration service can lock in your name within hours."}},
        {"@type":"Question","name":"How long does check company name availability UK take?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Using our real-time company names search, the check takes under 5 seconds. Our tool queries the Companies House API directly. Once you confirm your ltd company name is available, our formation process takes as little as 3-6 working hours for same-day registrations submitted before 3 PM UK time."}}
