        {"@type":"Question","name":"What is the current UK VAT registration threshold in March 2026?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The current UK VAT registration threshold in March 2026 is £90,000. This threshold has been confirmed frozen for the 2025/26 and 2026/27 tax years. Businesses whose taxable turnover exceeds £90,000 in any rolling 12-month period must register for VAT within 30 days."}},
        {"@type":"Question","name":"What is the UK standard VAT rate in 2026?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The UK standard VAT rate in 2026 is 20%. A reduced rate of 5% applies to certain goods such as home energy and children's car seats. A zero rate of 0% applies to most food, children's clothing, and books."}},
        {"@type":"Question","name":"What is the UK VAT registration threshold 2026?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The UK VAT registration threshold in 2026 is £90,000 of taxable turnover measured on a rolling 12-month basis. This applies to sole traders, limited companies, and partnerships. The deregistration threshold is £88,000."}},
        {"@type":"Question","name":"Do I need to register for VAT when I form a UK Ltd?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. VAT registration is separate from company formation. When you register a UK Limited Company at Companies House, you are not automatically VAT-registered. You must register with HMRC for VAT separately once your taxable turnover exceeds £90,000, or voluntarily at any point."}},
        {"@type":"Question","name":"Can a non-resident UK Ltd company owner register for VAT?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. VAT registration is based on the company's UK taxable turnover, not the director's residency. Non-resident owners of UK Ltd companies must register for VAT if their UK taxable turnover exceeds £90,000 in any 12-month period."}},
        {"@type":"Question","name":"What penalties apply for late VAT registration in the UK?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"HMRC penalties for late VAT registration range from 5% to 15% of the net VAT owed: up to 9 months late = 5%; 9–18 months late = 10%; over 18 months late = 15%. The minimum penalty is £50."}}
